1... Rxh2 wins a pawn and creates strong pressure on the h-file. If White plays 2. Rh1, Black has 2... Rxh1# (mate). Best defense is 2. Ke1, after which 2... Rg2 (or 2... Bxc5) gives Black a clear edge.

Black to move. I recommend 1... Ne4! (from f6 to e4).

Why this is strong:
- It immediately attacks White’s queen on d2.
- If White greedily plays 2. Qxc3, Black has 2... Nxc3, winning the White queen for a knight (and then 3. bxc3 leaves Black with a big material edge).
- If White retreats with 2. bxc3 (capturing the bishop on c3), Black can continue 2... Nxd2 3. Bxd2 and remains clearly ahead (queen vs minor piece advantage).

Sample lines:
- 1... Ne4 2. Qxc3 Nxc3 3. bxc3
- 1... Ne4 2. bxc3 Nxd2 3. Bxd2

- If you want to see all legal Black moves first, say: get_legal_moves
- If you want to inspect the board again, say: get_current_board
